-- Barclays names head for M&A of its U.S. financial practice
-- By Mike Stone
-- Mon May 12, 2014 06:39PM EDT
-- None



May 12 (Reuters) - Barclays Plc <BARC.L> said on Monday it had hired a Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N> veteran of 14 years to head up mergers and acquisitions for its Americas financial institutions practice.

The London-based bank said Tom Vandever will be a managing director and is to join the firm in August. Vandever was head of financial institutions at Goldman, where he completed over 100 transactions.